def media(I):
    ch = I.shape[2]
    med=np.zeros(ch,)
    for i in range(ch):
        med[i]=np.mean(I[:,:,i].ravel())
    return med
In [3]:
def mcov(I):
    nx,ny,ch = I.shape
    It=np.zeros((ch,nx*ny))
    for i in range(ch):
        It[i,:]=I[:,:,i].ravel()
    cova=np.cov(It)
    return cova
In [4]:
def mcovi(I,sx,sy):
    I=I.astype(float)
    nx,ny,ch = I.shape
    It=np.zeros((ch,len(sx)))
    for i in range(ch):
        It[i,:]=I[sx,sy,i].ravel()
    cova=np.cov(It)
    return cova
